==Battle==
Desert Barettas appear alone in the [[Yahnikurm Desert]], and may be somewhat challenging, especially if the party attacks with [[Magic (command)|magic]], as it does not have any weaknesses and has a pretty high [[Magic Defense (stat)|Magic Defense]] stat. Even though it looks physically armored, the monster has a lower [[Defense (stat)|Defense]] stat than Magic Defense.

===Strategy===
Desert Barettas have high enough physical defense that using physical attacks may not be efficient unless the [[party]] is sufficiently powerful. Despite their higher magic defense stat, magical attacks deal damage more consistently until the party significantly outlevels the Desert Baretta. Casting [[Protect (Final Fantasy)|Protect]], [[Blink (Final Fantasy)|Blink]], and [[Invis (Final Fantasy)|Invis]] to raise the party's Defense and [[Evasion]] may be useful to defend against its powerful attacks, if necessary. [[Temper (Final Fantasy)|Temper]], [[Saber (Final Fantasy ability)|Saber]], [[Haste (Final Fantasy)|Haste]], and the [[Giant's Gloves (Final Fantasy)|Giant's Gloves]] can help bolster a character's attack power to punch through the Desert Baretta's defenses with physical attacks.

